events.title: eGFR Measurement
events.description: The estimated Glomerular Filtration Rate (eGFR) was recorded at 78 mL/min, which is below the normal range of 90 - 120 mL/min, indicating potential chronic kidney disease (CKD).

events.title: Blood Pressure Measurement
events.description: Blood pressure was recorded at 149/76 mmHg, with the systolic value exceeding the normal threshold of 120 mmHg, suggesting hypertension.

events.title: Serum HDL Cholesterol Level
events.description: The serum HDL cholesterol level was measured at 0.96 mmol/L, which is below the normal range of 1.2 - 5 mmol/L, indicating a potential risk factor for cardiovascular disease.

events.title: Serum Cholesterol/HDL Ratio
events.description: The serum cholesterol/HDL ratio was recorded at 2.6 mmol/mmol, which may indicate an increased risk of cardiovascular issues, as lower ratios are generally preferred.
